\subsection{Species}\label{species}

In total, information from 3452 fishing trips was collected and
analyzed. The grand total catch from December 01, 2014 to November 30,
2015 was 80522 kg, made up of fffffff. Of all the fishing trips, 32\%
caught no fish. The most abundant family in terms of number was
Carangidae, with 37649 individuals caught (42\%,) followed by Clupeidae
with 21720 (24\%,) together making up 66\% of all specimens caught.
However, they make up a much smaller portion of the total catch weight
over the period, at 10122kg (12.6\%) and 1310kg (1.6\%) respectively, or
14.2\% together. Instead, a majority of the total catch weight was made
up of Scombridae with 41618kg (52\%) followed by Xiphiidae with 18955kg
(24\%) making up 75\% together.

A total of 11432 kg of Sardines and Sardine-like species were caught in
250 trips. Of these, 7757 kg (68\%) were caught opposite to the
container port. A total of 41618 kg of tuna species were caught, in 881
trips. The total catch for swordfish was 18955kg, 5005kg for sailfish,
and 1966kg for sharks. In contrast, the local populations of reef fish
species are making up only a small part of the catch (under 1\% each),
less than 1600 Kg per year.

11448kg of fish were caught in November, of which 8311kg (73\%) were
Tuna species, and 692kg (6\%) were sardine species. 5919kg of fish were
caught in December, of which 3761kg (64\%) were Tuna species, and 694kg
(12\%) were sardine species. 2303kg of fish were caught in May, of which
1330kg (58\%) were Tuna species, and 463kg (20\%) were sardine species.
9813kg of fish were caught in October, of which 7113kg (72\%) were Tuna
species, and 53kg (1\%) were sardine species. 15934kg of fish were
caught in January, of which 11390kg (71\%) were Tuna species, and 3479kg
(22\%) were sardine species. 5518kg of fish were caught in February, of
which 3162kg (57\%) were Tuna species, and 1817kg (33\%) were sardine
species. 1577kg of fish were caught in June, of which 0kg (0\%) were
Tuna species, and 67kg (4\%) were sardine species. 6741kg of fish were
caught in August, of which 540kg (8\%) were Tuna species, and 544kg
(8\%) were sardine species. 4352kg of fish were caught in April, of
which 2854kg (66\%) were Tuna species, and 1052kg (24\%) were sardine
species. 5664kg of fish were caught in September, of which 1423kg (25\%)
were Tuna species, and 225kg (4\%) were sardine species. 3935kg of fish
were caught in March, of which 1684kg (43\%) were Tuna species, and
1905kg (48\%) were sardine species. 7318kg of fish were caught in July,
of which 50kg (1\%) were Tuna species, and 441kg (6\%) were sardine
species.

